## المرحلة 8 — `DonorMedicalDocumentsController.cs` 🟢 [NEW]

### التفاصيل
Controller جديد كامل لخدمة `IDonorMedicalDocumentService`.

#### [NEW] `DonorMedicalDocumentsController.cs`

```
المسار: BloodConnectAPI/Controllers/DonorMedicalDocumentsController.cs
Route Base: api/medical-documents
```

**Endpoints:**

| Method | Route | Action | Auth |
|--------|-------|--------|------|
| `POST` | `/` | `UploadDocumentAsync` | `Donor` + `Admin` |
| `GET` | `/donor/{donorId}` | `GetByDonorIdAsync` | `Admin` |
| `GET` | `/{id}` | `GetByIdAsync` | `Admin` |
| `PATCH` | `/{id}/verify` | `VerifyDocumentAsync` | `Admin` |
| `DELETE` | `/{id}` | `DeleteAsync` | `Admin` |

**ملاحظات التنفيذ:**
- يحتاج `IWebHostEnvironment` لاستخراج `WebRootPath` وتمريره لـ `UploadDocumentAsync`
- الـ Upload يستخدم `[FromForm]` وليس `[FromBody]` لأن `SubmitMedicalDocumentDto` يحتوي على `IFormFile`
- `VerifyDocumentAsync` يستقبل `verifiedByUserId` من JWT Claims

```csharp
// Constructor
public DonorMedicalDocumentsController(
    IDonorMedicalDocumentService documentService,
    IWebHostEnvironment env,
    ILogger<DonorMedicalDocumentsController> logger)

// Upload
[HttpPost]
[Authorize]
[Consumes("multipart/form-data")]
public async Task<IActionResult> Upload([FromForm] SubmitMedicalDocumentDto dto)
{
    var uploadedBy = User.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)!;
    var rootPath = _env.WebRootPath;
    var response = await _documentService.UploadDocumentAsync(dto, rootPath, uploadedBy);
    ...
}

// Verify
[HttpPatch("{id}/verify")]
[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]
public async Task<IActionResult> Verify(int id, [FromBody] VerifyMedicalDocumentDto dto)
{
    var verifiedBy = User.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)!;
    var response = await _documentService.VerifyDocumentAsync(id, dto, verifiedBy);
    ...
}

// Delete
[HttpDelete("{id}")]
[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]
public async Task<IActionResult> Delete(int id)
{
    var rootPath = _env.WebRootPath;
    var response = await _documentService.DeleteAsync(id, rootPath);
    ...
}
```

